This paper deals with the issue of inappropriate content on YouTube, specifically targeting young children. The paper discusses building a classifier to detect such content, which falls under the category of machine learning and natural language processing (cs.CY). The paper also discusses the use of algorithms and recommendation systems on YouTube, which falls under the category of information retrieval (cs.IR). The paper also mentions the production and quality of videos, which falls under the category of multimedia (cs.MM). The paper also discusses the use of language and text in videos, which falls under the category of computational linguistics (cs.CL). Finally, the paper discusses the security and privacy concerns related to the content on YouTube, which falls under the category of cryptography and security (cs.CR).
